{
  "doc_id": "48609",
  "text": "Vascular cell adhesion molecule-1 (VCAM-1) and intercellular adhesion molecule-1 (ICAM-1) are mediators of endothelial-leukocyte adhesion in inflammatory states [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . They mediate tight binding and extravasation of leukocytes through endothelial cell junctions [CITATION_4] . Low levels of adhesion molecules are detected in serum of normal individuals and several investigators have recently documented increased levels in patients with sepsis and other critical illnesses [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . There is interest in examining serum levels of adhesion molecules in sepsis and other inflammatory conditions and relating their measurement to outcome from critical illness [CITATION_7] . Up-regulation of membrane-bound and soluble forms of adhesion molecules and their corresponding ligands on endothelial cells is induced by inflammatory mediators, such as TNF-α and IL-6. Soluble isoforms of adhesion molecules are critical for the early events of leukocyte recruitment [CITATION_8] .",
